experiment_description:
CXCR4 and CXCR5 receptor production and homeostasis reactions.
Modify the concentrations of CXCL12 and CXCL13 in the extracellular medium to explore the effect of receptor binding. 

Cell reactions: 

CXCR4 (CXCR5) molecules are produced (gene transcription) and degraded in the cytosol. Cytosolic CXCR4 (CXCR5) is transported to the plasma membrane where it becomes CXCR4| (CXCR5|) receptor. CXCR4| (CXCR5|) receptor and CXCL12:CXCR4| (CXCL13:CXCR5|) receptor complex are internalized and degraded. 

CXCR5 receptor production and recycling
rate = 0.4	gCXCR5 -> CXCR5 + gCXCR5
rate = 1	CXCR5 ->
rate = 3.3	CXCR5 -> CXCR5|
rate = 0.06	CXCR5| -> CXCR5
rate = 0.051	CXCL13:CXCR5| -> CXCL13:CXCR5
rate = 1	CXCL13:CXCR5 ->

CXCR4 receptor production and recycling
rate = 0.4	gCXCR4 -> CXCR4 + gCXCR4
rate = 1	CXCR4 ->
rate = 3	CXCR4 -> CXCR4|
rate = 0.054	CXCR4| -> CXCR4
rate = 0.027	CXCL12:CXCR4| -> CXCL12:CXCR4
rate = 1	CXCL12:CXCR4 ->

ECM reactions: 

GC B cell chemotaxis: ECM reactions
rate = 0.21	CXCL13:CXCR5| -> CXCL13 + CXCR5|
rate = 0.0077	CXCL13 + CXCR5| -> CXCL13:CXCR5|
rate = 0.494	CXCL12:CXCR4| -> CXCL12 + CXCR4|
rate = 0.042	CXCL12 + CXCR4| -> CXCL12:CXCR4|

reaction_complexes.description: A set of reactions that are needed by GC B cells for chemotaxis. These cells should be added to the ECM. Non-uniform distributions of ligand (CXCL13 and CXCL12) in the ECM will cause non-uniform concentrations of bound chemokine receptors (CXCR5| and CXCR4|) and non-uniform distributions of the pseudo-molecule A*. The magnitude and direction of the chemotactic force is proportional to the polarization of activated pseudo-molecule A*, which is proportional to the polarization of bound chemokine receptors (CXCL12:CXCR4| and CXCL13:CXCR5|).
